<br>
&quot;Hail adventurers!&quot; It boomed.<br>
&quot;What the hell is that?&quot; Mystdi cried.<br>
&quot;Do not be alarmed, for I am an ally,&quot; it replied.<br>
Zantes tried opening the left door, because he heard of The Adventurer's Left Hand Rule <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
&quot;Locked I'm afraid, Master Darkwood, but to get through you must answer my riddle,&quot; the statue said.<br>
&quot;More like three riddles mixed into one!&quot;<br>
&quot;Lets have it madam,&quot; Daloria replied.<br>
&quot;My first is only born once, but dies nine different times.  My Second is the heart of alarm, and my third can be found arranging locks of golden thread found on the morning caller's head.&quot;<br>
&quot;How much time do we have, statue?&quot; Zantes asked<br>
&quot;As much time as you like, well no...Untill your death.&quot;<br>
&quot;The first one is very easy!  Cat!&quot; Mystdi cried.<br>
&quot;Riddle number 2 is difficult,&quot; Daloria said.<br>
As Zantes looked at Mystdi he noticed her blonde hair.<br>
&quot;Number three is comb!&quot;  The third arranges hair!&quot;<br>
&quot;Very good Master Darkwood!&quot; the statue exclaimed.<br>
&quot;Now, heart, it can mean different things...Like core, center, or middle,&quot; Daloria thought in her head.<br>
She drew out the word alarm in the ground, &quot;A!&quot; she cried.<br>
The statue nodded.<br>
&quot;Catacomb,&quot; Zantes said.<br>
&quot;You three have good heads on your shoulders, you may proceed, but be warned, there may be sights that you don't want to see, so I recomend your friends staying here with me master darkwood,&quot; warned the statue.<br>
With that, the center and right hand door vanished with a flash.<br>
Zantes started hearing something in his head, &quot;Oh Zantes, we are sorry we didn't come home to you......&quot;<br>
He shook his head and opened the door to find jail cells.  No signs of life could be found, skeletons littered the cells.  Zantes saw two skeletons sitting against a wall, holding hands...A familiar prayer book was sitting in what looked like the woman's lap...They were Zantes' parents.<br>
A long cry could be heard throughout Odus that day, Zantes had found the truth and it would haunt him until his very own death. <p>Zantes Darkwood
